<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8" />
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
  <title><%= serviceName %> — Compassionate Capitalism Endpoint</title>
  <meta name="description" content="Centralized authentication microservice with RS256 JWTs, refresh token rotation, and JWKS distribution for distributed subsystems." />
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/styles.css" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.googleapis.com" />
  <link rel="preconnect" href="https://fonts.gstatic.com" crossorigin />
  <link href="https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@300;400;500;600;700&family=JetBrains+Mono:wght@400;500&display=swap" rel="stylesheet" />
</head>
<body>
  <header class="topbar">
    <div class="container topbar-inner">
      <a href="#" class="brand">
        <span class="brand-mark">⬢</span>
        <span class="brand-text"><%= serviceName %></span>
      </a>
      <nav class="topnav">
        <a href="#overview">Overview</a>
        <a href="#quickstart">Quickstart</a>
        <a href="#endpoints">API Reference</a>
        <a href="#integration">Integration</a>
        <a href="#security">Security</a>
        <a href="/health" class="pill">/health</a>
      </nav>
    </div>
  </header>

  <section class="hero">
    <div class="container hero-inner">
      <span class="eyebrow">Compassionate Capitalism Endpoint</span>
      <h1>Centralized authentication, distributed by design.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        A production-grade auth microservice that issues RS256 JSON Web Tokens
        and publishes its public key over JWKS so every subsystem — HR,
        Finance, Operations — can verify identities locally, with zero
        round-trips to a central authority.
      </p>
      <div class="hero-actions">
        <a class="btn btn-primary" href="#quickstart">Get started</a>
        <a class="btn btn-ghost" href="#endpoints">API reference</a>
      </div>
      <div class="hero-meta">
        <div class="meta-item"><strong>Algorithm</strong><span>RS256 / 2048-bit</span></div>
        <div class="meta-item"><strong>Discovery</strong><span>/.well-known/jwks.json</span></div>
        <div class="meta-item"><strong>Issuer</strong><span><%= issuer %></span></div>
        <div class="meta-item"><strong>Status</strong><span class="status-dot">Operational</span></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <main class="container">
    <!-- Overview -->
    <section id="overview" class="section">
      <h2>Overview</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        This service is the single source of identity for your platform. It
        owns user lifecycle, password policy, email verification, password
        reset, and token issuance. Downstream services never call it on the
        hot path — they verify tokens locally using the public key exposed
        at <code>/.well-known/jwks.json</code>.
      </p>

      <div class="grid grid-3">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Asymmetric trust</h3>
          <p>RS256 keypairs let subsystems verify tokens without holding any secret. Rotate keys without redeploying clients.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Refresh rotation</h3>
          <p>Long-lived opaque refresh tokens are rotated on every use and revoked on password change, reset, or deactivation.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Operational primitives</h3>
          <p>Email verification, password reset, account deactivation, JTI blacklisting, rate limiting, and structured logs out of the box.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Quickstart -->
    <section id="quickstart" class="section">
      <h2>Quickstart</h2>
      <p class="muted">From clone to a running service in under five minutes.</p>

      <ol class="steps">
        <li>
          <h4>1. Install dependencies</h4>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">npm install</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>2. Configure environment</h4>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">cp .env.example .env
# Edit DB_*, SMTP_*, ADMIN_API_KEY, JWT_ISSUER</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>3. Generate the RS256 keypair</h4>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">npm run keys:generate
# Writes keys/private.pem and keys/public.pem (chmod 600)</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>4. Run database migrations</h4>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">npm run migrate</code></pre>
        </li>
        <li>
          <h4>5. Start the service</h4>
<pre><code class="lang-bash">npm run dev      # development with auto-reload
npm start        # production</code></pre>
        </li>
      </ol>
    </section>

    <!-- Endpoints -->
    <section id="endpoints" class="section">
      <h2>API Reference</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        Base URL: <code><%= baseUrl %></code>. All request and response
        bodies are JSON. Errors follow
        <code>{ "error": { "code", "message" } }</code>.
      </p>

      <h3 class="group-title">Public</h3>
      <% publicEndpoints.forEach(function(ep) { %>
        <%- include('partials/endpoint', { ep: ep }) %>
      <% }) %>

      <h3 class="group-title">Authenticated</h3>
      <p class="muted small">Send <code>Authorization: Bearer &lt;access_token&gt;</code>.</p>
      <% protectedEndpoints.forEach(function(ep) { %>
        <%- include('partials/endpoint', { ep: ep }) %>
      <% }) %>

      <h3 class="group-title">Administrative</h3>
      <p class="muted small">Send <code>X-Admin-Api-Key: &lt;ADMIN_API_KEY&gt;</code>.</p>
      <% adminEndpoints.forEach(function(ep) { %>
        <%- include('partials/endpoint', { ep: ep }) %>
      <% }) %>
    </section>

    <!-- Integration -->
    <section id="integration" class="section">
      <h2>Integrating a subsystem</h2>
      <p class="muted">
        Subsystems verify access tokens locally using the public key from
        the JWKS endpoint. Cache the JWKS response and refresh on
        <code>kid</code> miss.
      </p>

      <div class="tabs">
        <button class="tab active" data-tab="node">Node.js</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="python">Python</button>
        <button class="tab" data-tab="go">Go</button>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel active" data-panel="node">
<pre><code class="lang-js">const jwt = require('jsonwebtoken');
const jwksClient = require('jwks-rsa');

const client = jwksClient({
  jwksUri: '<%= baseUrl %>/.well-known/jwks.json',
  cache: true,
  cacheMaxAge: 10 * 60 * 1000,
});

function getKey(header, cb) {
  client.getSigningKey(header.kid, (err, key) =>
    cb(err, key && key.getPublicKey())
  );
}

function verify(token) {
  return new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
    jwt.verify(
      token,
      getKey,
      { algorithms: ['RS256'], issuer: '<%= issuer %>' },
      (err, payload) => (err ? reject(err) : resolve(payload))
    );
  });
}</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="python">
<pre><code class="lang-python">import jwt
from jwt import PyJWKClient

JWKS_URL = "<%= baseUrl %>/.well-known/jwks.json"
jwks = PyJWKClient(JWKS_URL)

def verify(token: str) -> dict:
    signing_key = jwks.get_signing_key_from_jwt(token).key
    return jwt.decode(
        token,
        signing_key,
        algorithms=["RS256"],
        issuer="<%= issuer %>",
    )</code></pre>
      </div>

      <div class="tab-panel" data-panel="go">
<pre><code class="lang-go">import (
  "github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5"
  "github.com/MicahParks/keyfunc/v3"
)

k, _ := keyfunc.NewDefault([]string{"<%= baseUrl %>/.well-known/jwks.json"})

token, err := jwt.Parse(raw, k.Keyfunc,
  jwt.WithValidMethods([]string{"RS256"}),
  jwt.WithIssuer("<%= issuer %>"),
)</code></pre>
      </div>

      <h3>Token payload</h3>
<pre><code class="lang-json">{
  "sub": "42",
  "email": "user@example.com",
  "name": "Jane Doe",
  "iat": 1714000000,
  "exp": 1714000900,
  "iss": "<%= issuer %>",
  "jti": "8b1a9953-c761-4e78-9c1c-..."
}</code></pre>
    </section>

    <!-- Security -->
    <section id="security" class="section">
      <h2>Security model</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Password storage</h3>
          <p>Bcrypt with cost factor 12. Plaintext is never logged. Password change and reset both revoke all active refresh tokens.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Token revocation</h3>
          <p>Logout blacklists the access token's <code>jti</code> until its natural expiry. Refresh tokens are rotated on every use; reuse fails closed.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Email enumeration</h3>
          <p><code>/forgot-password</code> always returns success regardless of whether the address exists.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Transport &amp; rate limiting</h3>
          <p>Helmet sets strict security headers. Auth routes are rate-limited (50 req / 15 min / IP). Always terminate TLS at your edge.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Operations -->
    <section id="operations" class="section">
      <h2>Operations</h2>
      <div class="grid grid-2">
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Health check</h3>
          <p><code>GET /health</code> returns <code>{ status, uptime }</code>. Wire it to your load balancer and uptime monitor.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Logging</h3>
          <p>Structured JSON via Winston. Pipe stdout to your log aggregator (Datadog, Loki, CloudWatch).</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Key rotation</h3>
          <p>Generate a new keypair, bump <code>JWT_KID</code>, deploy. Subsystems pick up the new key on next JWKS refresh — no client redeploy required.</p>
        </article>
        <article class="card">
          <h3>Blacklist hygiene</h3>
          <p>Schedule <code>Blacklist.cleanup()</code> via cron to purge expired entries and keep the table compact.</p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

  <footer class="footer">
    <div class="container footer-inner">
      <div>
        <strong><%= serviceName %></strong>
        <p class="muted small">Compassionate Capitalism Endpoint · v<%= version %></p>
      </div>
      <div class="footer-links">
        <a href="/.well-known/jwks.json">JWKS</a>
        <a href="/health">Health</a>
        <a href="#endpoints">API</a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </footer>

  <script src="/js/app.js"></script>
</body>
</html>
